SECTION 3 THE LIE OF THE “THIRD OPTION”</p>
<p>It is necessary to take a moment to talk about the umbrella of 
options which some people try to use as an escape from the primary 
choice. The primary choice is between believing that morality doesn’t 
exist and believing that it does. All other purported options which 
deviate from a choice between the main two options, can be found under 
the umbrella of moral relativism. Moral relativism is the belief that 
there are an infinite number of different moralities. Moral relativism 
typically comes in two main forms: individual relativism and societal 
relativism.</p>
<p>Individual relativism is the belief that there are an infinite number
 of possible moralities which are based upon the infinite range of 
individuals who might hold them. This view means that we each have no 
responsibility for our actions. If we are beholden only to ourselves, 
how can we be responsible for anything? All of our whims and desires 
come from ourselves. If I myself am the standard by which I challenge 
those whims then there isn’t a filter between which desires are good or 
evil. How can we be expected to improve if what we want to do at any 
time is considered right? If being a serial killer gives me joy, who are
 you to tell me otherwise? After all, I create my own morality. I decide
 what’s right and wrong and you have no right to stop me. In my own 
experience I have found that allowing serial killers to do their own 
thing is not a peaceful stance.<br>
If someone believes in individual relativism, the only justification 
they have to stop me from doing whatever I want, is the fact that they 
might be stronger than me. This means that there’s no evil that would 
come from say, raping someone, because the stronger person felt it was 
good to do at the time and they create their own morality. Who is to say
 that what they did was wrong? Their victim certainly wasn’t strong 
enough to stop them. Does that mean they should be allowed to continue? 
Ah, but an individual relativist can’t use the word “should'' at all 
because to believe that every person creates their own morality is to 
believe that no outside opinion can inform them of a “better” way. There
 is no better way. There’s simply their way. Again, they create their 
own morality so whatever the strongest person believes is right, they’re
 allowed to do it simply because they believe it’s right and they have 
the ability to do it. There is no outside standard upon which they can 
be judged.</p></div></div></div></div><div class="Message_messageMetadataContainer__nBPq7"><span class="Message_messageMetadataText__FxY5_">5:14 AM</span></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="ChatMessage_chatMessage__xkgHx" data-complete="true" id="message-230685493205"><div class="LeftSideMessageHeader_leftSideMessageHeader__5CfdD"><div class="LeftSideMessageHeader_headerWrapper__EpVkV"><div class="BotMessageHeader_wrapper__gvvdw"><a class="BotHeader_title__cURS_" target="_blank" href=""><div class="Avatar_root__rwLF0 Avatar_rounded__qlug0 Avatar_xx-sm__hwmu_" data-pdl-avatar=""><img alt="Bot image for BotORFQ3TYM2O" data-deleted="true" loading="lazy" width="20" height="20" decoding="async" data-nimg="1" style="color: transparent;" src="Hello%20Gemini%2010_4_2025MoreComplete_files/defaultAvatar.7e5c73d2.png"></div><div class="BotHeader_textContainer__kVf_I"><p>BotORFQ3TYM2O</p></div></a></div></div></div><div class="ChatMessage_messageRow__DHlnq"><div></div><div class="ChatMessage_messageWrapper__4Ugd6"><div class="Message_rowWithFooter__FShU6"><div class="Message_row__ug_UU"><div class="Message_messageBubbleWrapper__sEq8z"><div class="Message_leftSideMessageBubble__VPdk6"><div class="Message_messageTextContainer__w64Sc"><div class="Message_selectableText__SQ8WH"><div class="Markdown_markdownContainer__Tz3HQ"><div class="Prose_prose__7AjXb Prose_presets_prose__H9VRM Prose_presets_theme-hi-contrast__LQyM9"><p><em>I
