<p>This being said, it is obvious that two people can have different 
perspectives and both be right. For instance, if there’s a wall between 
me and another person, and the wall on my side shows only clean-red 
brick and the wall on their side is covered in moss, we would both be 
right when we say that the wall is clean and, that the wall has moss. 
The same principle applies to morality. Everyone has different 
perspectives on what’s considered right and wrong, because none of us 
can see the full truth of the subject.<br>
This is a different concept from what moral relativists believe. The 
people espousing a belief in moral relativism don’t just say that people
 can have different perspectives on the topic of morality. Instead, they
 say that all people’s perspectives are entirely right in and of 
themselves. They say that the truth of the wall conforms to the 
individual. In our example this would be like saying that for me, the 
entire wall has clean brick on both sides with no moss whatsoever. 
Whereas for the other person, the entire wall is covered in moss on both
 sides.<br>
Neither of these possible truths is correct. The truth is that the wall 
is covered in moss on one side with clean brick on the other. The key is
 that we’re both talking about different aspects of the wall. I’m 
talking about the right side; the other person is talking about the left
 side. Both of these sides are aspects of the wall as a whole, which 
means we’re both correct when we attribute these smaller qualities to 
the wall. However, when we attempt to say that our interpretation of the
 wall is the whole truth in and of itself that’s when we run into 
issues. Regardless of what either one of us sees or experiences, there’s
 still a wall independent of our knowledge of it. It is this wall that 
we’re trying to come to understand through our communication with each 
other. If the wall truly conformed to its own infinity of possible 
interpretations, it couldn’t exist.<br>
Let me be clear here that as long as the wall exists in the realm of 
infinite possibility, the wall could be anything. It could be entirely 
clean or entirely covered in moss. It could be a tree, or a frog. The 
wall could be any color of the rainbow. It could even exist and not 
exist at the same time. When the wall exists in the realm of infinite 
possibility it does not exist in our reality. Nothing exists in our 
reality as an infinite. Anything that actually exists in our reality 
must be finite.<br>
Let’s say I promised to give you some chocolates. I didn’t tell you how 
many chocolates I would give you. It’s possible I could give you an 
infinite number of chocolates. Then, I provide you with 3 chocolates on 
your desk. These chocolates have now exited the realm of infinite 
possibility and entered actual existence for you. You know this because 
you can’t eat things in the realm of infinite possibility. You can only 
eat things that actually exist. You now have 3 chocolates. You do not 
have a million chocolates. You have 3. Sure, in some possible universe, 
if we dive back into the realm of infinite possibility, I could have 
given you a million chocolates. But, right now, in actual existence, you
 only have 3. If this concept is debated, I’ll start selling a year 
supply of burgers by only giving you one. I mean, after all, it’s my 
perception that I gave you a year’s supply so it must be true!</p></div></div></div></div><div class="Message_messageMetadataContainer__nBPq7"><span class="Message_messageMetadataText__FxY5_">5:17 AM</span></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="ChatMessage_chatMessage__xkgHx" data-complete="true" id="message-230686810069"><div class="LeftSideMessageHeader_leftSideMessageHeader__5CfdD"><div class="LeftSideMessageHeader_headerWrapper__EpVkV"><div class="BotMessageHeader_wrapper__gvvdw"><a class="BotHeader_title__cURS_" target="_blank" href=""><div class="Avatar_root__rwLF0 Avatar_rounded__qlug0 Avatar_xx-sm__hwmu_" data-pdl-avatar=""><img alt="Bot image for BotORFQ3TYM2O" data-deleted="true" loading="lazy" width="20" height="20" decoding="async" data-nimg="1" style="color: transparent;" src="Hello%20Gemini%2010_4_2025MoreComplete_files/defaultAvatar.7e5c73d2.png"></div><div class="BotHeader_textContainer__kVf_I"><p>BotORFQ3TYM2O</p></div></a></div></div></div><div class="ChatMessage_messageRow__DHlnq"><div></div><div class="ChatMessage_messageWrapper__4Ugd6"><div class="Message_rowWithFooter__FShU6"><div class="Message_row__ug_UU"><div class="Message_messageBubbleWrapper__sEq8z"><div class="Message_leftSideMessageBubble__VPdk6"><div class="Message_messageTextContainer__w64Sc"><div class="Message_selectableText__SQ8WH"><div class="Markdown_markdownContainer__Tz3HQ"><div class="Prose_prose__7AjXb Prose_presets_prose__H9VRM Prose_presets_theme-hi-contrast__LQyM9"><p><em>My
