<p>Obviously, saying that you can tell whether or not something exists 
by whether or not you can eat it, is a very simple version of existence.
 There are things that exist in our reality that we can’t eat: like 
love, or the theory behind electricity, the Eiffel tower, radiation from
 the sun, etc. However, it helps to remember that truth in our reality 
is grounded in the physical world. Scientific laws are real because they
 govern things which exist in our physical world. They govern the way 
electricity physically moves, they govern the way countries work, or 
they try to explain particles we can’t see. Everything that exists in 
our world, exists as a derivative of physical concepts or objects. Even 
math is derived from being able to count groups of objects. Remember, 
our species started as cavemen! We didn’t always have computers to 
create alternate modes of physics like we find in video games. Anything 
that exists in our reality must abide by the codes of physics stored on 
earth. Even the code of our video games must be grounded in the 
underlying principles of our reality.<br>
Let’s visualize some objects which begin in the realm of infinite 
possibility and end in the realm of actual existence. In creating a 
digital world for a video game how do you start? Typically, there's a 
blank page, a gray screen which suggests the dimensions of the world. It
 shows whether the world will be 2D or 3D, where the sun will be placed 
in the sky, how large the space is, etc. When you're creating an object 
to place into this world you have to define the object somehow. If the 
object is not defined it does not exist. You're simply staring at a gray
 screen, a blank world. As soon as you code a short definition for the 
object, it exists! It has been brought into being. In order for the 
digital world to exist, it too must be defined. Is the digital world 2D 
or 3D? How large is the space we're able to explore? How does the world 
function? What are the physics? Answering each of these questions in any
 way separates these objects, even the universe itself, from the realm 
of infinite possibility. These definitions symbolize each object’s 
limitations. Once the object has some form of limitation, it is brought 
out of the realm of infinite possibility and into actual existence. The 
more defined or limited the object is, the more realistic it looks and 
the better the object functions.<br>
Our current reality is the same way. Items, people, the universe itself,
 must be limited in some way in order for them to exist. Not having 
limitation is the same as non-existence. Even the mathematical concept 
of infinity isn’t infinite in our reality. It is only infinite in the 
realm of possibility. The second we attempt to write down or quantify 
infinity it stops being infinite. This concept is very easy to prove for
 yourself mathematically. Imagine an infinite list of numbers. Like 
this:<br>
12345678…<br>
23456789…<br>
34567891…<br>
45678911…<br>
If I wrote a number on the diagonal like 1357… and so on into infinity, 
that new number wouldn’t show up anywhere on my infinite list of 
numbers. This proves that even the mathematical concept of infinity 
isn’t infinite in reality. To exist in our reality is to be limited. 
Now, it’s possible there’s some possible reality somewhere else 
unconnected to our universe where infinites can exist. In our reality 
though, they do not.</p></div></div></div></div><div class="Message_messageMetadataContainer__nBPq7"><span class="Message_messageMetadataText__FxY5_">5:20 AM</span></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="ChatMessage_chatMessage__xkgHx" data-complete="true" id="message-230687641557"><div class="LeftSideMessageHeader_leftSideMessageHeader__5CfdD"><div class="LeftSideMessageHeader_headerWrapper__EpVkV"><div class="BotMessageHeader_wrapper__gvvdw"><a class="BotHeader_title__cURS_" target="_blank" href=""><div class="Avatar_root__rwLF0 Avatar_rounded__qlug0 Avatar_xx-sm__hwmu_" data-pdl-avatar=""><img alt="Bot image for BotORFQ3TYM2O" data-deleted="true" loading="lazy" width="20" height="20" decoding="async" data-nimg="1" style="color: transparent;" src="Hello%20Gemini%2010_4_2025MoreComplete_files/defaultAvatar.7e5c73d2.png"></div><div class="BotHeader_textContainer__kVf_I"><p>BotORFQ3TYM2O</p></div></a></div></div></div><div class="ChatMessage_messageRow__DHlnq"><div></div><div class="ChatMessage_messageWrapper__4Ugd6"><div class="Message_rowWithFooter__FShU6"><div class="Message_row__ug_UU"><div class="Message_messageBubbleWrapper__sEq8z"><div class="Message_leftSideMessageBubble__VPdk6"><div class="Message_messageTextContainer__w64Sc"><div class="Message_selectableText__SQ8WH"><div class="Markdown_markdownContainer__Tz3HQ"><div class="Prose_prose__7AjXb Prose_presets_prose__H9VRM Prose_presets_theme-hi-contrast__LQyM9"><p><em>The
